<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11092i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11092i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11092i"> 92(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> homo simplex in / vitalitate, duplex in / humanitate </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Latin <i>Homo simplex in vitalitate, duplex in humanitate</i>, Man is simple by the fact that he is alive, duplicitous by the fact that he is human. In his work <i>Raports du physique et du moral de l&apos;homme</i> of 1811, Maine de Biran attacked the incomplete vision represented by Boerhaave&apos;s phrase.</mm> </dd></dl>
